Pillboxes time. KC's offense vs HOU. Random 6 OL snap to start our 6th drive, with Burton in. Was a pass too. Weird. Jet got SO much more run than Pacheco this game. Watson remains Robinson 2.0. Moore with only two touches, both runs. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/rDDXOogEBG

On to the Defense. Watson and Williams splitting drives again. Only 3 total WR's for HOU is reflected in DB snap counts. Chenal got extra snaps for same reason, I assume. Gay only gave up one drive to Harris, and not even the entire drive! Progress?! 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/sfas7NlZ07

Houston's charts. 3 wide receivers, and they split the non-11p snaps between a second RB and a second (or third) TE. On defense, they had 7 different DB's with snaps. Was there an injury I don't remember? 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/UJkOxFzjOh

Day 56: Today I looked into play-by-play data available through #nflverse to come up with the top players by Red Zone volume and their TD conversion pct. Basically, how often do they convert Red Zone chances into TDs?
